==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin verb ''[[probare]]'', "to [[test]]", "to [[try]]", "to [[examine]]".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /pruːv/

===Verb===
'''to prove''' (''past tense:'' '''proved''', ''past participle:'' '''proved''' ''or'' '''proven''' (where ''proved'' is the older form))

#''(transitive)'' to [[demonstrate]] that something is [[true]]; to give [[proof]] for
#''(intransitive)'' to [[turn out]]
#:''Her method '''proved''' more efficient than his.''

